node.text: These three inspired the world, and gave me the courage to become an astronaut. Skill and bravery, Apollo11 on the Moon, 52 years ago today.

node.text: The mosquitos and I just had a fine view of the @Space_Station. Wistful, to know that place so well.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Chris Hadfield on July 17, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: The greatest telescope we've ever built is back in action after fixing a main computer problem. Well done the @nasahubble team!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Chris Hadfield on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 19 people, people standing and text.

node.text: From 18 to 82, all of these humans visiting & living in space this month. Next launch on Tuesday - Godspeed!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Chris Hadfield in Rhineland, Germany. May be a closeup.

node.text: Everywhere it's red, there's flooding - the Ruhr, Rhine and Meuse Rivers. Terrible consequence, with loss of life and property. Be safe, all. (space image to help emergency crews, from @europeanspaceagency)
